$ Windows Driver Kit
@ WDK

The WDK is an integrated environment and provides the tools to develop, build, test, deploy and debug → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/drivers[drivers].

{ Installing the WDK

  { Verifying if the WDK is already installed

    ? The presence of → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Vsix/VSyyyy/WDK_vsix[`%WindowsSdkDir%\Vsix\WDK.vsix`] indicates that the WDK is installed.

    If the WDK is installed can also be checkt with → Windows/settings[Settings] -> Apps & features.

  }
  { Steps to install the WDK 

    Summary of → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/download-the-wdk

    The WDK requires → Windows/development/Visual-Studio[Visual Studio].

    Start → Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Microsoft-Visual-Studio/Installer/vs_installer_exe[`vs_installer.exe`]

    Choose workload *Desktop development with C++*

    choose workload *Universal Windows Platform development*
    -
    In the right hand side, under *Optional*, choose *Windows 10 SDK (10.0.18362.0)*

     Choose tab *Individual components*, section *Compilers, build tools, and runtimes* to
    install *spectre mitigated libraris*

    Click modify to apply changes.

    Download `wdksetup.exe` from → https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2085767[]


  }

}
